# No Terminal — Auto Deploy Everything

The user **never uses the terminal**. Never ask them to run commands, install tools, or fix deploy issues manually.

## After every code change

When you finish a task that modifies project files, **automatically** sync to GitHub and Vercel before ending your response:

1. Run `bash scripts/sync-deploy.sh "commit message"` from the project root.
2. If the script fails, diagnose and fix it yourself (secrets, auth, build errors). Do not hand steps to the user.
3. Confirm both destinations in your reply:
   - GitHub: https://github.com/PedroSousa008/world-choir-app
   - Vercel: https://world-choir-app.vercel.app

## Never do this

- Do not say "run this in your terminal" or "you can push when ready"
- Do not leave uncommitted work at the end of a task unless the user explicitly asked not to deploy
- Do not commit secrets (`.env*`, API keys, tokens)

## Project references

- GitHub remote: `origin` → `https://github.com/PedroSousa008/world-choir-app.git`
- Branch: `main`
- Vercel project: `world-choir-app` (GitHub-connected; push triggers deploy)
- Node/Vercel CLI (if needed): `.tools/node-v22.22.0-darwin-arm64/bin`

## Commit messages

Write clear, concise messages focused on **why** the change was made.
